⊕meta⊕
name = "import-sky-library"
description = "Validate and import a folder of foreign/legacy .sky files into a target dir one-by-one: lint each, skip any that fail lint or already exist, gate the import manually, then write a kept/rejected/skipped manifest and verify the imports."
trigger.manual = true
output_style = "terse"
⊕⊕

※enumerate※
enumerate — list SOURCE/*.sky; fail if dirs missing or no candidates. No edges.
※※

§enumerate§
bash_file = "./scripts/enumerate.sh"
§§

※validate※
validate — lint each candidate; stage PASS to /tmp, log FAIL+codes, mark SKIP. depends_on=["enumerate"], trigger_rule=all_done.
※※

§validate§
depends_on = ["enumerate"]
bash_file = "./scripts/validate.sh"
§§

※gate※
gate — manual approval gate; shows PASS/FAIL/SKIP sets before mutation. depends_on=["validate"], trigger_rule=all_done. Waits on manual channel (1h timeout).
※※

§gate§
depends_on = ["validate"]
wait.channel = "manual"
wait.prompt = "Review the PASS (will import), FAIL (lint errors, rejected), and SKIP (already exists) sets above. Approve to copy the PASS files into the target dir."
wait.timeout = "1h"
§§

※finalize※
finalize — copy each staged PASS into TARGET (never overwrite); print kept/skipped manifest. depends_on=["gate"], trigger_rule=all_done.
※※

§finalize§
depends_on = ["gate"]
bash_file = "./scripts/finalize.sh"
§§

※verify※
verify — re-lint every imported file; rm /tmp staging list; exit nonzero if any file broken. depends_on=["finalize"], trigger_rule=all_done.
※※

§verify§
depends_on = ["finalize"]
bash_file = "./scripts/verify.sh"
§§

※※
# import-sky-library

Validate and import foreign/legacy .sky files from a SOURCE folder into a
TARGET .sky workflows dir, one file at a time. Each candidate is linted; only
lint-clean files that do NOT already exist in the target are staged for import.
A manual gate shows the kept / rejected / skipped sets before any file is
copied. After import, every newly-copied file is re-linted to confirm it is
clean in its new home.

Pure bash. No Claude node. No tokens consumed.

DAG:

    enumerate            list SOURCE/*.sky, fail if none / dirs missing
        |
    validate             lint each; PASS -> /tmp staging list (mktemp),
        |                FAIL -> log + codes, SKIP -> already in TARGET
        |
    gate   (manual)      show PASS/FAIL/SKIP; approve to import
        |
    finalize             cp each staged PASS into TARGET unless it exists;
        |                print kept / skipped manifest
        |
    verify               sky lint each imported file; rm the staging list;
                         exit nonzero if any imported file is broken

Run:

    sky run import-sky-library --var source=/path/to/foreign/dir --var dir=.sky/workflows

Vars:

    source  ($SKY_SOURCE)  directory holding the foreign/legacy .sky files to import.
    dir     ($SKY_DIR)     target .sky workflows directory to import into.

Nodes:

    enumerate  list SOURCE/*.sky; fail fast if a dir is missing or no candidates.
    validate   lint each candidate; stage PASS to /tmp, log FAIL+codes, mark SKIP.
    gate       manual approval gate; shows PASS/FAIL/SKIP before any mutation.
    finalize   copy each staged PASS into TARGET (never overwrite); print manifest.
    verify     re-lint every imported file; rm the /tmp staging list; fail if broken.

Notes:

  - A file is REJECTED (not imported) if `sky lint` fails on it; its error
    codes are logged so you can fix the source and re-run.
  - A file is SKIPPED if a same-named file already exists in the target dir;
    this workflow never overwrites. Remove/rename the target file and re-run
    to replace it.
  - Staging uses a mktemp file under /tmp; verify removes it with a plain `rm`
    (no `rm -f`), so no permission gate is needed.
※※
